1274
01:38:46.650 --> 01:38:49.639
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Reverse the order, but… Do you agree?

1275
01:38:53.680 --> 01:39:00.660
Mike: Perhaps we should… Although I do not know if the prisoner will be helpful anymore.

1276
01:39:02.870 --> 01:39:04.000
Mike: But we could, ….

1277
01:39:04.520 --> 01:39:05.369
Tim Sackton: by now.

1278
01:39:05.550 --> 01:39:09.680
Mike: suggestions weren't off. But… We could bring them out again.

1279
01:39:10.030 --> 01:39:12.700
Mike: I mean, we could… Bring them out of the mirror, right?

1280
01:39:14.290 --> 01:39:14.850
Tim Sackton: Yeah.

1281
01:39:16.230 --> 01:39:16.780
Mike: And….

1282
01:39:18.550 --> 01:39:22.109
David S. Kong: Just have, like, a quick telepathic, like, sidebar for a second.

1283
01:39:22.620 --> 01:39:25.090
David S. Kong: … So, what, what, I mean…

1284
01:39:26.380 --> 01:39:31.640
David S. Kong: What are we trying to do here? Like… Shouldn't we just go and… Kill the Empress?

1285
01:39:33.490 --> 01:39:39.930
Mike: Well, Kenzo, I'm a big believer in our strength and power, but she has 4,000 hubgoblins with her.

1286
01:39:40.340 --> 01:39:42.359
David S. Kong: Can we separate her from the army?

1287
01:39:42.950 --> 01:39:44.279
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That is a good question.

1288
01:39:46.540 --> 01:39:51.409
David S. Kong: I mean, isn't this one of those, kill the Empress and then the 4,000 Hobglobins are kind of like, oh shit, and then…

1289
01:39:52.360 --> 01:39:54.729
David S. Kong: What do they, what do they do after their leader's dead?

1290
01:39:56.600 --> 01:39:58.200
Mike: We supply them with a new leader.

1291
01:39:59.000 --> 01:40:04.580
Mike: I think we supply them with a new leader, and then… and then they go off and make a peace treaty with the humans, yeah.

1292
01:40:04.580 --> 01:40:13.129
David S. Kong: Yeah, but, but, I mean, shouldn't we figure out how to just… like, why, why, like, killing 4,000 Hopgoblins and the Empress is pretty hard, but killing just the Empress?

1293
01:40:13.740 --> 01:40:15.279
David S. Kong: Maybe a little bit more manageable.

1294
01:40:16.070 --> 01:40:18.729
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I mean, I agree, it's just hard to imagine a way to separate her.

1295
01:40:25.640 --> 01:40:33.670
David S. Kong: I mean, we knocked one of the hobgoblins off the centipede, and she flew back by herself and, like, scouted around, you know?

1296
01:40:34.720 --> 01:40:36.159
David S. Kong: Didn't seem that hard.

1297
01:40:37.170 --> 01:40:42.549
Mike: But she was only… A couple… not even a couple hundred feet from our troops, right?

1298
01:40:45.730 --> 01:40:47.680
Mike: I don't know if she would have gone further.

1299
01:40:51.850 --> 01:40:53.750
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Can you teleport someone unwillingly?

1300
01:40:53.750 --> 01:40:58.469
Mike: I was just literally thinking that. I know we can't… Teleport is not. Scatter?

1301
01:40:59.240 --> 01:41:00.410
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Plane shift?

1302
01:41:01.110 --> 01:41:02.700
Mike: Plain?

1303
01:41:03.510 --> 01:41:05.109
Mike: Plainshift is willing.

1304
01:41:05.890 --> 01:41:12.439
Mike: … Scatter is unwilling, but it's only 120 feet.

1305
01:41:16.970 --> 01:41:23.290
Mike: You know what would be a good spell? Oh, but Seeker can cast whatever spell. Force Cage, the one that, …

1306
01:41:24.090 --> 01:41:29.729
Mike: The one that… The wind collar cast on us, the cage that surrounded us.

1307
01:41:32.620 --> 01:41:40.359
Mike: The question is, if she's trapped in something like a force cage, why do we think her army won't stop and come and kill us?

1308
01:41:42.210 --> 01:41:44.100
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Or that she won't just dispel it.

1309
01:41:44.910 --> 01:41:47.509
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It can't be… force cage can't be… It can't be designed.

1310
01:41:47.510 --> 01:41:49.210
Mike: Fort Bay can't be dispelled.

1311
01:41:50.480 --> 01:41:50.880
David S. Kong: That'd be….

1312
01:41:50.880 --> 01:41:52.249
Mike: an 8th level spell.

1313
01:41:53.200 --> 01:41:54.350
David S. Kong: How do we get out of that?

1314
01:41:54.710 --> 01:41:56.830
Mike: We did it, remember? We talked our way out.

1315
01:41:56.830 --> 01:41:59.190
Tim Sackton: You… you talked your way out, you just waited.

1316
01:41:59.770 --> 01:42:02.750
Mike: The only… you CAN use magical…

1317
01:42:02.930 --> 01:42:06.350
Mike: You can attempt to magically escape, but you have to make a save.

1318
01:42:06.620 --> 01:42:07.300
David S. Kong: Hmm.

1319
01:42:12.080 --> 01:42:19.109
Mike: So… I just… I wonder if it would be easier to separate her.

1320
01:42:20.460 --> 01:42:21.920
Mike: In the chaos of a battle.

1321
01:42:25.400 --> 01:42:26.100
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): bread.

1322
01:42:27.000 --> 01:42:27.630
Mike: Right?

1323
01:42:28.820 --> 01:42:36.390
David S. Kong: Tim, when we were checking out the Hopping Goblin Army, were there any obvious, like, you know, super strong, you know, lieutenant-type guys, you know?

1324
01:42:36.730 --> 01:42:41.469
Tim Sackton: Not that you saw, but it was hard to tell, right? I mean, it's…

1325
01:42:44.920 --> 01:42:48.590
Tim Sackton: mostly they were cloaked by ash, right? The ash was…

1326
01:42:49.810 --> 01:42:56.970
Tim Sackton: you could see sort of vague shapes, you couldn't see much detail. You only really got a good look at the Empress because she flew out.

1327
01:42:58.180 --> 01:42:58.730
Mike: Right.

1328
01:42:58.730 --> 01:43:01.900
Tim Sackton: go try and… See what happened to her.

1329
01:43:03.220 --> 01:43:07.240
Tim Sackton: When… when she got the report that two Hobgoblins, like, mysteriously.

1330
01:43:14.200 --> 01:43:15.349
David S. Kong: Must be, …

1331
01:43:15.570 --> 01:43:19.710
David S. Kong: I feel like we've been doing a good job of doing creative things recently, instead of just, like, you know…

1332
01:43:20.310 --> 01:43:21.659
David S. Kong: Punching our way through.

1333
01:43:23.870 --> 01:43:24.900
David S. Kong: There's gotta be a way to….

1334
01:43:24.900 --> 01:43:33.730
Mike: I mean, I could cast Dream every night on her, and if she keeps failing her save, she takes 36 damage every night, and can't regain spells.

1335
01:43:35.310 --> 01:43:36.340
David S. Kong: Oh? That's….

1336
01:43:36.750 --> 01:43:40.170
Mike: I don't know, you… oh yeah, no benefit from the rest.

1337
01:43:40.640 --> 01:43:45.020
Mike: I mean, we could do all kinds of things to try and, you know, make her life unpleasant.

1338
01:43:45.620 --> 01:43:46.850
David S. Kong: Hell yeah, let's do that.

1339
01:43:47.320 --> 01:43:48.119
David S. Kong: That's cool.

1340
01:43:48.770 --> 01:43:51.940
Mike: Yeah, I tried it with Fausto, but he kept making it safe.

1341
01:43:53.580 --> 01:43:57.070
Tim Sackton: No, Fasta's Tower. Fasta's… wrong planet.

1342
01:43:57.510 --> 01:43:58.459
Mike: Right, right, right, right, right.

1343
01:43:58.460 --> 01:44:02.750
David S. Kong: She's probably got some, like, chaos Metal Protects-me-from-everything type thing, too.

1344
01:44:02.750 --> 01:44:05.359
Tim Sackton: I mean, you have no idea if she even sleeps or not.

1345
01:44:05.360 --> 01:44:06.769
Mike: She may never sleep.

1346
01:44:06.850 --> 01:44:08.519
David S. Kong: Oh, Hobgoblins don't sleep?

1347
01:44:08.810 --> 01:44:09.570
Mike: Wow.

1348
01:44:09.570 --> 01:44:14.420
Tim Sackton: No, but the hobgoblin you talked to was like, she's been alive for 100 years.

1349
01:44:14.420 --> 01:44:20.880
Mike: She might be, like, infused with Chaos Metal, and it's, like, taken, like, who knows? It might be power, right? Like….

1350
01:44:20.880 --> 01:44:21.970
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yeah….

1351
01:44:22.920 --> 01:44:25.140
Mike: Like, you know, Terminator 2 never slapped, right?

1352
01:44:25.140 --> 01:44:27.440
David S. Kong: Yeah, she's like Tetsuo from A Cure or something.

1353
01:44:27.720 --> 01:44:33.890
Mike: Yeah, exactly. So, we could try it, but she may never actually… Sleep.

1354
01:44:34.880 --> 01:44:35.550
Mike: ….

1355
01:44:35.550 --> 01:44:38.810
David S. Kong: … Yeah, maybe there's no way to separate her from the army, huh?

1356
01:44:42.850 --> 01:44:52.919
Mike: I mean… That simple-minded plan… With no cleverness, is to simply… set up a big battle.

1357
01:44:53.220 --> 01:44:53.590
David S. Kong: Yeah.

1358
01:44:53.590 --> 01:44:56.230
Mike: And then… So wait, Pete, are you, like….

1359
01:44:56.430 --> 01:45:04.310
Tim Sackton: This has got… you've gotten a little bit distracted from the council. Are you sidebarring out of character, or what's going on here?

1360
01:45:04.310 --> 01:45:10.179
Mike: No, no, no, no, no, this was a telepathic sidebar from Kenza, but that was, I'll stop for a minute and say we should… we should include the council in this conversation.

1361
01:45:10.180 --> 01:45:10.970
David S. Kong: Okay, okay, okay.

1362
01:45:10.970 --> 01:45:15.299
Mike: And we'll switch to… we, like, were telepathically, like, our eyes were darting around.

1363
01:45:15.300 --> 01:45:15.780
Tim Sackton: Here's work.

1364
01:45:15.780 --> 01:45:16.340
Mike: talking, right?

1365
01:45:16.340 --> 01:45:17.050
David S. Kong: But….

1366
01:45:17.050 --> 01:45:24.499
Mike: dealt with all saying we should include the… and then saying we've… we've been discuss… just, we'll say, we've been discussing some options here.

1367
01:45:25.110 --> 01:45:27.559
Mike: But we should include you in our deliberations.

1368
01:45:29.820 --> 01:45:36.330
Tim Sackton: Martin… Martin stands up and says, I would…

1369
01:45:37.390 --> 01:45:39.510
Tim Sackton: Love to hear what you propose.

1370
01:45:44.470 --> 01:45:54.439
Tim Sackton: Dimkala, When… Do you think the stone board might arrive, and in what strength?

1371
01:45:54.860 --> 01:45:58.289
Tim Sackton: Seems useful information for our planning purposes.

1372
01:46:01.290 --> 01:46:04.389
Tim Sackton: And the stoneborn turns and looks and says.

1373
01:46:08.320 --> 01:46:11.649
Tim Sackton: I have ridden… Through several nights.

1374
01:46:12.320 --> 01:46:14.589
Tim Sackton: To bring you this news.

1375
01:46:18.290 --> 01:46:20.060
Tim Sackton: Even the fastest of us.

1376
01:46:20.570 --> 01:46:22.010
Tim Sackton: Must muster.

1377
01:46:22.780 --> 01:46:25.580
Tim Sackton: And reach the battlefield with strength to fight.

1378
01:46:26.690 --> 01:46:30.040
Tim Sackton: It is… A week.

1379
01:46:30.210 --> 01:46:32.569
Tim Sackton: For you can expect us in force.

1380
01:46:37.200 --> 01:46:40.180
Tim Sackton: Do we know? He says, looking around the room.

1381
01:46:42.620 --> 01:46:45.120
Tim Sackton: When the Hobgoblins might arrive.

1382
01:46:45.660 --> 01:46:46.689
Mike: 6 days.

1383
01:46:48.740 --> 01:46:53.920
Tim Sackton: 6 days to reach… The heart, or the plateau?

1384
01:46:58.140 --> 01:47:01.970
Mike: Our prisoner was… Not clear on that point.

1385
01:47:03.190 --> 01:47:07.749
Mike: It seems his empress has held her battle plans relatively close.

1386
01:47:12.480 --> 01:47:16.819
Tim Sackton: Though… Halfling looks up at this point.

1387
01:47:18.100 --> 01:47:20.859
Tim Sackton: I, she says, …

1388
01:47:25.070 --> 01:47:28.870
Tim Sackton: Unless they are traveling at some exceptional rate, I…

1389
01:47:31.240 --> 01:47:34.470
Tim Sackton: It seems hard to believe they could be 6 days from the…

1390
01:47:37.670 --> 01:47:38.740
Tim Sackton: Heart Root.

1391
01:47:39.410 --> 01:47:46.120
Tim Sackton: That's… 60, 70 miles from the plateau edge.

1392
01:47:46.240 --> 01:47:48.030
Tim Sackton: by the crow flies.

1393
01:47:48.490 --> 01:47:52.329
Tim Sackton: And that's going through forests more if you follow a clear path.

1394
01:47:56.530 --> 01:47:57.830
Tim Sackton: Are they really?

1395
01:47:58.440 --> 01:47:59.690
Tim Sackton: Traveling?

1396
01:48:00.170 --> 01:48:01.640
Tim Sackton: At such a speed?

1397
01:48:02.650 --> 01:48:11.469
Tim Sackton: They are far enough away now, at least, that our scouts cannot see them from watchtowers along the plateau edge.

1398
01:48:13.140 --> 01:48:18.899
Tim Sackton: So they must be… 100 miles off the plateau, at least.

1399
01:48:18.900 --> 01:48:19.379
Mike: I mean….

1400
01:48:19.380 --> 01:48:20.030
Tim Sackton: more?

1401
01:48:20.030 --> 01:48:24.220
Mike: We have little… don't we have little… illusionary little

1402
01:48:24.900 --> 01:48:26.849
Mike: Yeah. Showing exactly where they are?

1403
01:48:27.040 --> 01:48:32.510
Tim Sackton: She looks, and she says, Wow.

1404
01:48:33.330 --> 01:48:35.890
Tim Sackton: We, of course, don't know their rate of travel.

1405
01:48:36.120 --> 01:48:38.800
Tim Sackton: That is the crucial variable to calculate.

1406
01:48:39.130 --> 01:48:40.490
Tim Sackton: their arrival.

1407
01:48:44.940 --> 01:48:45.570
Tim Sackton: Yes.

1408
01:48:45.570 --> 01:48:46.160
Mike: Wow.

1409
01:48:52.290 --> 01:48:57.830
Tim Sackton: If they are expected to… be 6 days.

1410
01:48:59.770 --> 01:49:04.310
Tim Sackton: As the crow flies… from…

1411
01:49:10.270 --> 01:49:16.500
Tim Sackton: From the… HeartRoot itself… Must be traveling.

1412
01:49:19.680 --> 01:49:21.899
Tim Sackton: Almost 40 miles a day?

1413
01:49:23.930 --> 01:49:27.319
Tim Sackton: Did they seem to be going that fast to you when you watched them?

1414
01:49:28.090 --> 01:49:30.400
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Our scouts have not gotten close.

1415
01:49:32.060 --> 01:49:38.700
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): What's my take if Wolpe's gonna do, like, his best estimate based on his scouting skills and nature and mapping and all that stuff?

1416
01:49:38.990 --> 01:49:45.439
Tim Sackton: The big unknown, from Welby's point of view, the big unknown is if they're traveling 24 hours a day, or if they're resting.

1417
01:49:45.680 --> 01:49:46.370
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Hmm.

1418
01:49:47.310 --> 01:49:47.670
Tim Sackton: there.

1419
01:49:47.670 --> 01:49:48.210
Mike: Wow.

1420
01:49:49.070 --> 01:49:50.449
Mike: A guy would know that.

1421
01:49:51.680 --> 01:49:52.380
Tim Sackton: Yeah.

1422
01:49:52.620 --> 01:49:57.159
Tim Sackton: If they're… if they're traveling… They were not going…

1423
01:49:57.610 --> 01:50:04.690
Tim Sackton: So, if they were traveling, say, 12 hours a day, then 40 miles a day implies

1424
01:50:05.590 --> 01:50:10.979
Tim Sackton: They're going something like… Between 3 and 4 miles per hour.

1425
01:50:11.220 --> 01:50:12.230
Tim Sackton: like, a…

1426
01:50:12.900 --> 01:50:20.570
Tim Sackton: good walking pace. They were moving slower than that, right? It was… you could walk… you could definitely have walked faster than them.

1427
01:50:21.680 --> 01:50:22.959
Tim Sackton: than the Beast.

1428
01:50:24.440 --> 01:50:28.550
Tim Sackton: Like, probably it was… it was going more like…

1429
01:50:30.390 --> 01:50:33.820
Tim Sackton: 1 to 2 miles an hour. Like, it seems slow to you.

1430
01:50:34.920 --> 01:50:36.930
Tim Sackton: But of course, if it's going…

1431
01:50:37.040 --> 01:50:40.400
Tim Sackton: If they're traveling 24 hours a day, then…

1432
01:50:41.000 --> 01:50:44.930
Tim Sackton: 40 miles that they could easily be making 40 miles a day.

1433
01:50:47.770 --> 01:50:48.650
Mike: M.

1434
01:50:49.540 --> 01:50:50.750
Mike: Perhaps we should.

1435
01:50:51.530 --> 01:50:53.340
Mike: Bring our prisoner into this.

1436
01:50:55.510 --> 01:51:01.360
Mike: He may not be as willing to be interrogated as he was earlier, but…

1437
01:51:04.000 --> 01:51:05.729
Mike: Do I actually… do I have any spells left?

1438
01:51:06.090 --> 01:51:14.640
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Is the only question that we have, are they traveling 24 hours a day? Do we need to know more than that? Do we have other ways to get that? Can we, like, augury, or consult gods, or…?

1439
01:51:14.640 --> 01:51:17.159
Mike: Well, sure, but I could also just detect thoughts.

1440
01:51:17.780 --> 01:51:19.449
Mike: I could read his thoughts.

1441
01:51:20.830 --> 01:51:21.600
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yeah.

1442
01:51:22.180 --> 01:51:22.900
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That's fair.

1443
01:51:23.200 --> 01:51:26.440
Tim Sackton: I mean, you could also just ask… Tatanshi.

1444
01:51:26.780 --> 01:51:29.690
Tim Sackton: I'm saving that until we have a few more questions. Oh, okay.

1445
01:51:30.330 --> 01:51:31.969
Tim Sackton: Does detect thoughts work?

1446
01:51:32.660 --> 01:51:39.049
Tim Sackton: I… You probably have to actually release him, you have to actually release him from the mirror.

1447
01:51:39.350 --> 01:51:40.809
Mike: Correct, yes.

1448
01:51:41.990 --> 01:51:43.490
David S. Kong: Can't you cast Suggestion again?

1449
01:51:44.630 --> 01:51:45.650
Mike: I could.

1450
01:51:49.050 --> 01:51:55.360
Mike: But Detect Thoughts actually seems potentially even more useful, because I could… He's…

1451
01:51:55.570 --> 01:51:58.570
Mike: Very unlikely to make a DC20 Wisdom safe.

1452
01:51:58.910 --> 01:51:59.500
Tim Sackton: Right.

1453
01:51:59.800 --> 01:52:03.349
Mike: And… If he fails to save, I can, like…

1454
01:52:03.480 --> 01:52:09.200
Mike: Probe his brain for things that… He doesn't say, right?

1455
01:52:10.050 --> 01:52:11.139
David S. Kong: We like her brand, bro.

1456
01:52:24.220 --> 01:52:33.209
Mike: I mean, it can try and break my… he can make an Intelligence Arcana check to stop me, but again, DC20, I'm not that worried.

1457
01:52:33.550 --> 01:52:36.870
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): All of this is good, it's worth asking, let's keep it in our pocket.

1458
01:52:37.300 --> 01:52:40.890
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But does it meaningfully change the plans we're making?

1459
01:52:41.810 --> 01:52:45.779
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Or, like, the question of how do we separate the leader from the army?

1460
01:52:46.890 --> 01:52:51.860
Tim Sackton: if… It meaningfully changes the plans, only in the sense that if

1461
01:52:52.990 --> 01:52:56.360
Tim Sackton: He looks over at Zimcala. If the Stoneborn arrive…

1462
01:52:58.060 --> 01:53:00.759
Tim Sackton: Changes the calculus of battle, no?

1463
01:53:01.220 --> 01:53:04.359
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But we're not gonna not fight them if the Stoneborne don't arrive.

1464
01:53:04.770 --> 01:53:06.290
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It's just gonna go worse.

1465
01:53:07.790 --> 01:53:08.650
Tim Sackton: Fair.

1466
01:53:09.400 --> 01:53:10.289
David S. Kong: So here's the thing.

1467
01:53:10.690 --> 01:53:11.569
David S. Kong: Here's the thing.

1468
01:53:13.170 --> 01:53:14.430
David S. Kong: The Empress?

1469
01:53:14.600 --> 01:53:15.850
David S. Kong: Well powerful.

1470
01:53:16.000 --> 01:53:17.989
David S. Kong: And… we respect them.

1471
01:53:18.860 --> 01:53:22.869
David S. Kong: … I feel confident.

1472
01:53:23.040 --> 01:53:25.940
David S. Kong: My colleagues and I can handle the Empress.

1473
01:53:27.260 --> 01:53:35.110
David S. Kong: Now… If we're able… In this situation, and what we've gathered as well from The Hobbobins?

1474
01:53:35.520 --> 01:53:42.359
David S. Kong: This appears to be a situation where, upon the death of the Empress, the Hobgoblin army may…

1475
01:53:43.410 --> 01:53:49.070
David S. Kong: Surrender, run away, etc. It's very… it feels, this is… this is a very, …

1476
01:53:49.210 --> 01:53:53.199
David S. Kong: Top-heavy organization, at least as it relates to this… this army.

1477
01:53:54.030 --> 01:53:59.790
David S. Kong: If we're able to separate the Empress, if the five of us can, or if the four of us can.

1478
01:53:59.920 --> 01:54:05.799
David S. Kong: the five of us pointing it, for, Seeker 4. If the five of us, can…

