Mike: … Firestorm is not a point you can see, it's just a point. It creates 10 cylinders of fire.

2482
03:14:47.710 --> 03:14:51.370
Mike: That just burn people that do, like, quite a bit of damage.

2483
03:14:51.720 --> 03:14:55.525
Mike: … Ehhh…

2484
03:14:59.650 --> 03:15:06.240
Mike: We could… Tsunami's a good one.

2485
03:15:06.530 --> 03:15:07.860
Mike: …

2486
03:15:08.130 --> 03:15:15.099
Mike: Those are, like, the best 3, Sunbursts. I mean, that's 4 right there. Whirlwind, Firestorm, Sunburst, …

2487
03:15:15.800 --> 03:15:16.470
Mike: Tsunami?

2488
03:15:16.470 --> 03:15:19.060
David S. Kong: What level are those? Are those all 7th level spells?

2489
03:15:19.060 --> 03:15:19.590
Tim Sackton: Anthony.

2490
03:15:20.170 --> 03:15:21.659
Mike: Between 7th and 8th.

2491
03:15:21.760 --> 03:15:24.229
Mike: But Seeker would have to use his wish every day.

2492
03:15:24.230 --> 03:15:29.720
Tim Sackton: They're all Wish, they all require Seeker's 9th level slot, because nobody knows any of those spells.

2493
03:15:29.720 --> 03:15:30.480
Mike: Correct.

2494
03:15:31.360 --> 03:15:33.010
David S. Kong: Cool, let's do it. I like it.

2495
03:15:33.290 --> 03:15:40.180
Tim Sackton: Okay, so… You spend the afternoon plotting and planning.

2496
03:15:40.890 --> 03:15:50.880
Tim Sackton: And before we wrap for tonight, let's take 10 minutes or so to… include the conversation with Marcella.

2497
03:15:51.070 --> 03:15:59.270
Tim Sackton: As you settle in, To camp this night, after having made plans and sent a lot of messages.

2498
03:15:59.650 --> 03:16:03.380
Tim Sackton: And have a strategy for the next day.

2499
03:16:05.010 --> 03:16:07.440
Tim Sackton: Settle down just to catch up a little bit.

2500
03:16:10.890 --> 03:16:16.560
Tim Sackton: She looks… first thing she said, like, as you sit, she's… I mean, she's super grateful, she's like…

2501
03:16:20.180 --> 03:16:25.769
Tim Sackton: It was a… It was… it was just a gas.

2502
03:16:29.240 --> 03:16:35.590
Tim Sackton: Maybe you'd get my message, and maybe you'd come, and… I can't.

2503
03:16:38.480 --> 03:16:43.419
Tim Sackton: I am… I don't know what's gonna happen, but… I am…

2504
03:16:43.750 --> 03:16:46.390
Tim Sackton: I'm deeply grateful that you are here.

2505
03:16:49.970 --> 03:16:59.809
Tim Sackton: But, let's… Not talk of… the future now, I'd love to hear What's happening in Chardon?

2506
03:17:01.050 --> 03:17:17.350
Tim Sackton: Heard some rather crazy rumors about… Bosto and… The Academy falling apart, and… Riots, and… And…

2507
03:17:17.780 --> 03:17:24.040
Tim Sackton: How is Hector, and how is Vola, and… How's everybody doing?

2508
03:17:27.950 --> 03:17:31.980
David S. Kong: … Fasto's dead. Chardon…

2509
03:17:36.730 --> 03:17:38.050
David S. Kong: Reorganizing.

2510
03:17:38.380 --> 03:17:40.040
David S. Kong: Emperor trying his best.

2511
03:17:43.770 --> 03:17:49.229
David S. Kong: Shaylight… Hopefully soon, out of the hands of the oligarchs.

2512
03:17:53.490 --> 03:17:55.290
David S. Kong: Potential for some justice.

2513
03:17:56.630 --> 03:17:57.870
David S. Kong: 50-50.

2514
03:18:00.420 --> 03:18:04.930
Mike: your… Duh, duh.

2515
03:18:05.410 --> 03:18:13.240
Mike: those have… Those of your friends who had been caught in the… magic of…

2516
03:18:14.660 --> 03:18:18.570
Mike: Fausto's corruption have all been released from it.

2517
03:18:22.190 --> 03:18:23.600
Tim Sackton: That's good to hear.

2518
03:18:24.270 --> 03:18:26.530
Mike: Hector is with us.

2519
03:18:27.030 --> 03:18:33.640
Mike: … He should be here soon, as we said, he's traveling with our ship.

2520
03:18:33.920 --> 03:18:40.520
Mike: Vola… wished to… Escape bad memories.

2521
03:18:45.040 --> 03:18:48.469
Tim Sackton: We left her… where did we leave her? Tok? Did we leave her in Tokyo? I can't remember where we left her.

2522
03:18:50.850 --> 03:18:57.670
Tim Sackton: G… Left Chardon to go towards Aporia, and see what she found.

2523
03:19:03.460 --> 03:19:04.470
Tim Sackton: It seems…

2524
03:19:07.770 --> 03:19:11.080
Tim Sackton: Well… I can't complain.

2525
03:19:11.330 --> 03:19:16.920
Tim Sackton: And… Hadmos and Cassian?

2526
03:19:17.330 --> 03:19:18.629
Tim Sackton: Brought to justice?

2527
03:19:19.750 --> 03:19:20.470
Mike: Yes.

2528
03:19:22.980 --> 03:19:27.120
Mike: They are… Garmin.

2529
03:19:29.850 --> 03:19:30.980
Mike: They did not.

2530
03:19:32.350 --> 03:19:36.729
Mike: Unlike… Many, they were… true believers.

2531
03:19:37.690 --> 03:19:39.000
Mike: They did not.

2532
03:19:39.840 --> 03:19:41.829
Mike: Seek or wish for.

2533
03:19:43.140 --> 03:19:44.659
Mike: A second chance.

2534
03:19:46.330 --> 03:19:47.120
Tim Sackton: Oh.

2535
03:19:48.120 --> 03:19:51.910
Tim Sackton: I know, Catmosa's mask came off there towards the end.

2536
03:19:54.160 --> 03:20:01.799
Tim Sackton: When we first met you, I was… certain I was gonna be…

2537
03:20:04.820 --> 03:20:11.560
Tim Sackton: Well… Nobody ever clearly explained what… consequences were.

2538
03:20:13.810 --> 03:20:15.500
Tim Sackton: Said something about…

2539
03:20:22.100 --> 03:20:28.389
Tim Sackton: Do it, or… You won't remember your failures.

2540
03:20:29.380 --> 03:20:31.719
Tim Sackton: Because you won't even be yourself anymore.

2541
03:20:35.050 --> 03:20:36.509
Tim Sackton: It's a bad time. Yeah.

2542
03:20:38.690 --> 03:20:41.079
Tim Sackton: But he's… dead, I hope?

2543
03:20:42.110 --> 03:20:42.820
Mike: Yes.

2544
03:20:50.050 --> 03:20:51.740
Tim Sackton: She kind of sighs.

2545
03:20:57.700 --> 03:20:59.260
Tim Sackton: I'm glad to hear there's…

2546
03:20:59.860 --> 03:21:04.629
Tim Sackton: Some chance of justice in that city, I… I don't think I'm ever going back.

2547
03:21:07.570 --> 03:21:08.559
David S. Kong: Give it a year.

2548
03:21:11.500 --> 03:21:13.590
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): How has life been for you here?

2549
03:21:16.650 --> 03:21:18.260
Tim Sackton: It's been good.

2550
03:21:21.380 --> 03:21:28.399
Tim Sackton: The people here, it's not… It's a small community, and…

2551
03:21:30.770 --> 03:21:36.639
Tim Sackton: Pretty… insular in some ways, but… They're very welcoming.

2552
03:21:36.750 --> 03:21:37.949
Tim Sackton: Of those who…

2553
03:21:42.580 --> 03:21:49.419
Tim Sackton: Wish to join, anyway. Come not trying to make waves, but… learn their ways.

2554
03:21:52.230 --> 03:21:56.080
Tim Sackton: And the Rangers… You know, I joined up.

2555
03:21:56.220 --> 03:22:06.350
Tim Sackton: And… Trying to put my skills to some better use than… In the service of… Cadmos, out of fear.

2556
03:22:06.450 --> 03:22:07.890
Tim Sackton: Trying to do something.

2557
03:22:09.090 --> 03:22:15.199
Tim Sackton: Out of… I don't know if joy is the right word, but…

2558
03:22:19.000 --> 03:22:22.940
Tim Sackton: Well, it's nice when… People are grateful, right?

2559
03:22:29.860 --> 03:22:32.360
Tim Sackton: So, I've been at Planklands a bit.

2560
03:22:32.800 --> 03:22:34.260
Tim Sackton: Fought some monsters.

2561
03:22:35.090 --> 03:22:36.259
Tim Sackton: Survived it.

2562
03:22:37.560 --> 03:22:39.829
Tim Sackton: Nothing like what you've done, I'm sure.

2563
03:22:43.110 --> 03:22:48.729
Tim Sackton: traveled with… A few interesting folks.

2564
03:22:51.870 --> 03:22:55.210
Tim Sackton: Not many halflings, but… Daisy.

2565
03:22:55.370 --> 03:22:57.730
Tim Sackton: She's got an interesting story.

2566
03:22:59.830 --> 03:23:01.990
Tim Sackton: Should ask her about it sometime.

2567
03:23:02.300 --> 03:23:03.080
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): There we go.

2568
03:23:05.930 --> 03:23:08.840
Tim Sackton: She's quite eager for revenge on the Hotgoblins.

2569
03:23:12.940 --> 03:23:15.140
Tim Sackton: It's been… yeah, it's been good.

2570
03:23:16.530 --> 03:23:20.579
Tim Sackton: So… Home I never thought I'd find when I was…

2571
03:23:21.910 --> 03:23:24.590
Tim Sackton: Just doing everything out of fear.

2572
03:23:28.580 --> 03:23:29.619
Tim Sackton: How about you?

2573
03:23:31.890 --> 03:23:37.390
Tim Sackton: You seem like… You've made quite a name for yourselves.

2574
03:23:41.100 --> 03:23:42.610
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): We've got up to some things.

2575
03:23:44.760 --> 03:23:46.659
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Saw a lot of new places.

2576
03:23:47.750 --> 03:23:53.550
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Seemed for a minute there like it was quieting back down again, but … Maybe not.

2577
03:23:56.990 --> 03:24:01.680
Tim Sackton: Yeah, I don't know, this… Never…

2578
03:24:03.520 --> 03:24:05.730
Tim Sackton: heard of anything like this, I guess…

2579
03:24:06.580 --> 03:24:11.859
Tim Sackton: since the War of the Ashen Horde, maybe 30 years ago.

2580
03:24:18.240 --> 03:24:20.440
Tim Sackton: But… We'll get through it.

2581
03:24:24.220 --> 03:24:26.599
Tim Sackton: When did you get a flying castle, by the way?

2582
03:24:27.770 --> 03:24:29.219
Tim Sackton: I'm excited to see that.

2583
03:24:31.620 --> 03:24:38.269
Mike: It was… Not long after…

2584
03:24:42.940 --> 03:24:44.680
Mike: We left you, I think.

2585
03:24:56.750 --> 03:25:02.690
Mike: After, after we… after we left Charted, The first time.

2586
03:25:07.230 --> 03:25:14.540
Tim Sackton: Bobby, I… I'm sure that you have… many powerful

2587
03:25:14.740 --> 03:25:21.730
Tim Sackton: Magic now, and she looks down at her boots, these… Boots are of… I hope no.

2588
03:25:21.920 --> 03:25:27.170
Tim Sackton: big loss to you. They, I must say, have acquired some sentimental value for me.

2589
03:25:28.440 --> 03:25:33.260
Tim Sackton: But I… I will offer them back, if you would like them.

2590
03:25:35.690 --> 03:25:39.409
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yeah, trade you back, at least… at least for this week,

2591
03:25:42.640 --> 03:25:46.829
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): These boots, … Are not too slow themselves.

2592
03:25:50.080 --> 03:25:50.650
Tim Sackton: Hmm.

2593
03:25:51.650 --> 03:25:53.890
Tim Sackton: Wait, where did you get the Boots of Speed?

2594
03:25:58.850 --> 03:26:02.090
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I don't- wait, are those hers? I thought she'd, ….

2595
03:26:02.350 --> 03:26:06.649
Tim Sackton: No, you let her keep all her magic items. They might have been Hector's, the Boots of Speeds were Hector's, I think.

2596
03:26:07.050 --> 03:26:09.100
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Does she have boots of haste?

2597
03:26:13.240 --> 03:26:17.519
Tim Sackton: She did not have any… you gave her the boots of false tracks.

2598
03:26:17.960 --> 03:26:19.419
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Pulse tracks, that's right.

2599
03:26:19.660 --> 03:26:25.260
Tim Sackton: But they were agatas, you gave them to her, and she used them… that was part of how she escaped.

2600
03:26:25.920 --> 03:26:28.880
Tim Sackton: By pretending to be kobold tracks.

2601
03:26:30.420 --> 03:26:34.500
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I'll tell her, no, no, no, keep, keep them, keep them. Those are yours.

2602
03:26:35.070 --> 03:26:38.089
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I leave fewer and fewer tracks anyways these days.

2603
03:26:39.620 --> 03:26:40.740
Tim Sackton: Thank you.

2604
03:26:43.020 --> 03:26:43.870
Tim Sackton: Wow.

2605
03:26:46.580 --> 03:26:50.960
Tim Sackton: Feel like it's gonna be a busy… Weak.

2606
03:26:52.530 --> 03:26:54.289
Tim Sackton: I think I will turn in soon.

2607
03:26:59.010 --> 03:27:02.309
Tim Sackton: Happy to… Catch up anytime, and…

2608
03:27:02.950 --> 03:27:06.430
Tim Sackton: Certainly let me know when Hector gets here, I'm sure I will be.

2609
03:27:08.360 --> 03:27:15.349
Tim Sackton: I'm sure I'll be very busy, and… in a… Need a hand or two.

2610
03:27:15.930 --> 03:27:22.459
Tim Sackton: Rangers in the fight, and… At some point, we'll have to talk tactics and see what we can do.

2611
03:27:23.460 --> 03:27:25.329
Tim Sackton: They help you the most.

2612
03:27:28.260 --> 03:27:31.120
Tim Sackton: For tonight, let's just get some rest, and…

2613
03:27:33.570 --> 03:27:35.369
Tim Sackton: There will be battles in the morning.

2614
03:27:36.260 --> 03:27:36.940
Tim Sackton: Yeah?

2615
03:27:39.750 --> 03:27:40.460
Mike: Yeah?

2616
03:27:43.870 --> 03:27:51.280
Tim Sackton: kind of… Gives you a nod, like… raises her… water, glass, and… Toast.

2617
03:27:53.130 --> 03:27:56.699
Tim Sackton: Leaves you to your rest as she walks off to…

2618
03:27:56.900 --> 03:27:59.650
Tim Sackton: catch up with. She seems to know a bunch of people.

2619
03:27:59.910 --> 03:28:02.360
Tim Sackton: camps, and she walks off to catch up with people.

2620
03:28:06.550 --> 03:28:07.719
Tim Sackton: We'll end there.

2621
03:28:08.870 --> 03:28:14.470
Tim Sackton: As you drift off for the night, And we'll pick up again.

2622
03:28:16.140 --> 03:28:18.189
Tim Sackton: On… when's our next session?

2623
03:28:22.530 --> 03:28:23.300
Mike: Go now.

2624
03:28:23.660 --> 03:28:24.829
Tim Sackton: September 11th.

2625
03:28:25.040 --> 03:28:27.970
Mike: I was gonna say, it's not for a while, it's after Burning Man.

2626
03:28:27.970 --> 03:28:28.940
Tim Sackton: After Burning Man.

2627
03:28:30.800 --> 03:28:33.069
David S. Kong: Night of my colonoscopy. Exciting.

2628
03:28:33.070 --> 03:28:33.750
Mike: Bright.

2629
03:28:33.750 --> 03:28:35.750
Tim Sackton: So, pick up then.

2630
03:28:36.530 --> 03:28:43.420
Tim Sackton: And then we'll see how things go, and whether we need to use the… Extra session we've got scheduled.

2631
03:28:43.900 --> 03:28:47.999
Mike: Do we only have… Two more sessions between now and….

2632
03:28:48.300 --> 03:28:49.110
Tim Sackton: No.

2633
03:28:49.360 --> 03:28:50.979
Mike: I was gonna say, we should have another….

2634
03:28:50.980 --> 03:28:57.459
Tim Sackton: There's a bunch scheduled, but there's more that you have to do before we get to Nantucket than just kill the Empress Kid.

2635
03:28:57.460 --> 03:28:58.170
Mike: Yeah.

2636
03:28:58.550 --> 03:29:04.560
Tim Sackton: We've got one… 2… We've got 3 scheduled.

2637
03:29:04.780 --> 03:29:08.099
Tim Sackton: Before Nantucket, plus one extra if we need that.

2638
03:29:08.480 --> 03:29:09.140
Mike: Right.

2639
03:29:10.800 --> 03:29:11.890
Mike: Alright.

2640
03:29:11.890 --> 03:29:13.860
David S. Kong: Okay, good night, everybody.

2641
03:29:14.150 --> 03:29:15.140
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Good, yo.

